President Muhammadu Buhari has commiserated with the Arewa Consultative Forum over the passing of its National Publicity Secretary, Emmanuel Yawe. In a statement signed on Saturday by his Special Adviser on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, titled ‘President Buhari mourns ACF spokesman, Emmanuel Yawe’, Buhari prayed that God will comfort the loved ones of the deceased. The statement read, “The President commiserates with family members, friends and associates of Yawe, particularly in the media, where he served meritoriously as a reporter and editor of various publications for many years. Excerpts Of Inaugural Lecture 359, OAU, Ile Ife Delivered By… Adebayo Pegs Nigeria’s Free Trade Zone Cumulative Investments At… “President Buhari prays that the Almighty God will receive the soul of the departed and comfort all his loved ones.”